<subSubSection id="C3496520B149C06FFF62FCF5466BC396" pageId="4" pageNumber="53" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BEC36ABB149C06FFF62FCF5414BC306" blockId="4.[151,1437,895,1390]" pageId="4" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis id="B927EAB9B149C06FFF62FCF54246C4B6" box="[151,347,895,921]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="53">Male macroptera</emphasis>
. Smaller than female (
<figureCitation id="13682A2EB149C06FFDA9FCF541B2C4B5" box="[604,687,895,922]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–17" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[203,1385,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-29@6.[203,1385,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 10–17. A. japonicas (10) Body of female; (11) Body of male; (12) Antenna of female; 13–17 Male. (13) Antennae; (14) Head, promotum, meso and metanotum; (15) Maxillary palp; (16) Ternites VIII–X; (17) Ternites I–II." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6581572" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6581572/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="53">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
); antennal segment II pale, III pale at base and brown on the apex half (
<figureCitation id="13682A2EB149C06FFF23FC294231C491" box="[214,300,931,958]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–17" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[203,1385,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-29@6.[203,1385,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 10–17. A. japonicas (10) Body of female; (11) Body of male; (12) Antenna of female; 13–17 Male. (13) Antennae; (14) Head, promotum, meso and metanotum; (15) Maxillary palp; (16) Ternites VIII–X; (17) Ternites I–II." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6581572" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6581572/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="53">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
); all femora brown, tibiae pale at base half and light brown rest, tarsi brown. Maxillary palps 3- segmented, segment II undivided (
<figureCitation id="13682A2EB149C06FFDE8FC4D416CC4CD" box="[541,625,967,994]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–17" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[203,1385,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-29@6.[203,1385,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 10–17. A. japonicas (10) Body of female; (11) Body of male; (12) Antenna of female; 13–17 Male. (13) Antennae; (14) Head, promotum, meso and metanotum; (15) Maxillary palp; (16) Ternites VIII–X; (17) Ternites I–II." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6581572" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6581572/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="53">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
). Abdominal tergite I with two longitudinal ridges (
<figureCitation id="13682A2EB149C06FFB4DFC4D4616C4CD" box="[1208,1291,967,994]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–17" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[203,1385,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-29@6.[203,1385,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 10–17. A. japonicas (10) Body of female; (11) Body of male; (12) Antenna of female; 13–17 Male. (13) Antennae; (14) Head, promotum, meso and metanotum; (15) Maxillary palp; (16) Ternites VIII–X; (17) Ternites I–II." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6581572" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6581572/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="53">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
), IX without tubercles and clasper, S1 setae longer than S2 (
<figureCitation id="13682A2EB149C06FFD54FC6141E9C329" box="[673,756,1003,1030]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–17" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[203,1385,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-29@6.[203,1385,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 10–17. A. japonicas (10) Body of female; (11) Body of male; (12) Antenna of female; 13–17 Male. (13) Antennae; (14) Head, promotum, meso and metanotum; (15) Maxillary palp; (16) Ternites VIII–X; (17) Ternites I–II." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6581572" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6581572/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="53">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
). Sternites II–VIII with 3 or 4 pairs of posteromarginal setae, VIII with 1 pair of discal setae laterally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEC36ABB149C06FFF32FBBE469EC35D" blockId="4.[151,1437,895,1390]" pageId="4" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis id="B927EAB9B149C06FFF32FBBE426BC361" bold="true" box="[199,374,1076,1102]" pageId="4" pageNumber="53">Measurements</emphasis>
(male in microns). Body length 1424; head length 144, width 160. Pronotum length 159, width 181. Fore wing length 658, median width 94. Antennal segments I–IX length: 27, 47, 107, 93, 57, 40, 33, 12, 11.
</paragraph>
